⭐⭐⭐⭐☆ Question 74/120 – posexplode()

🎤 Interview Question

Write PySpark code to explode the skills array while also displaying the position of each skill.


---

📊 Input Dataset

emp_id	skills

101	["Python","SQL","Spark"]



---

✅ Expected Output

emp_id	position	skill

101	0	Python
101	1	SQL
101	2	Spark



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import posexplode

df.select(
    "emp_id",
    posexplode("skills").alias("position", "skill")
).show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Difference between explode() and posexplode()?

Answer

explode() returns only the value.

posexplode() returns both the array index (position) and the value.



---

Q2. When is posexplode() useful?

Answer

When the order of array elements matters, such as ranked recommendations or ordered event sequences.


---

Q3. Does indexing start from 0?

Answer

Yes. Array positions are zero-based.


