⭐⭐⭐⭐⭐ Question 76/120 – Flatten Nested Arrays

🎤 Interview Question

You are given a DataFrame where each employee has an array of project names.

Write PySpark code to flatten the array so that each project appears in a separate row.


---

📊 Input Dataset

emp_id	projects

101	["Banking","Retail"]
102	["Healthcare"]
103	["Finance","Insurance","E-Commerce"]



---

✅ Expected Output

emp_id	project

101	Banking
101	Retail
102	Healthcare
103	Finance
103	Insurance
103	E-Commerce



---

✅ Recommended Solution

from pyspark.sql.functions import explode

df.select(
    "emp_id",
    explode("projects").alias("project")
).show()


---

🎤 Most Asked Interview Questions

Q1. Is flattening arrays different from explode()?

Answer

For a single array column, flattening is typically done using explode().


---

Q2. Why do we flatten arrays?

Answer

Many downstream operations (joins, aggregations, filters) work more naturally on one value per row than on arrays.


---

Q3. Where is this used?

Answer

API response processing

Event logs

Product categories

Customer interests

Survey responses

